President Obama has declared a major disaster in California due to an earthquake that occurred between August 24 and September 7, 2014. Federal aid will be provided to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected area. The counties of Napa and Solano will receive federal funding for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Additional counties and forms of assistance may be designated after further assessments are completed. Stephen M. De Blasio Sr. has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the area.